President of the Nigerian Society of Engineers (NSE), Babagana Mohammed, has canvassed the need to build the country on different fronts. Mohammed, who was sworn in as the 32nd national president of the Society in Abuja, made the assertion in his acceptance speech. “We will align with the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) 2030 and ensure the engineering profession gives its best in national development,” he said.  The event was attended by Borno State Governor Babagana Zulum and members of his cabinet most of whom are engineers, Governor of Yobe State, Mai Buni, among others.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .